               <head>Final concord; Bedingfield, etc.; 1313</head>
               <msContents>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_105173">Bedingfield</placeName> etc. <origDate when="1313">1313</origDate>. 
                        Final agreement between <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> of <surname>Gislyngham</surname></persName>, and <persName nymRef="Gislyngham">
                           <forename>Alianor</forename>, his wife</persName>, plaintiffs, and <persName nymRef="Tendrynge">
                           <forename>Ralph</forename>, son of <persName>
                              <forename>John</forename> of <surname>Tendrynge</surname></persName>, 'chinaler'</persName>, and <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> le <surname>Spenser</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_113001">Thorndon (Thornedoun)</placeName></persName>, deforciants, by which the latter grant to the former, nine messuages, a toft, 220 acres of land, 13 acres of meadow, 23.5 acres of pasture, 70 acres of wood, and 36 shillings rent, in <placeName key="place_105173">Bedingfield (Bedyngfelde)</placeName>, <placeName key="place_105480">Rishangles</placeName>, <placeName key="place_105165">Aspall (Aspale)</placeName>, <placeName key="place_113000">Gislingham (Gislyngham)</placeName>, and <placeName key="place_113040">Hempnall Hall (Thornham Pilcoke)</placeName>, for themselves and their direct heirs, with remainder to <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> of <surname>Gislyngham</surname></persName>, for life, and then to other heirs of the said John.
                        Completed, within 3 weeks of Easter [April 12], 23 Ed. III [1349].
                        John and Alianora being represented by <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Waryn</surname></persName>, Ralph and Richard by <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Northwelde</surname></persName>.
                        Enrolled in Trinity term: Kell[shull]. 
                        <!--CHK what is this?: [J.C.P.]-->
                     </p>
